subSubSection.paragraph:
Pronotum (
Fig. 1
), in dorsal view, with anterior margin broadly rounded, posterior margin slightly excavated; surface without setae, with transverse striae, except on anterior third; lateral margins convergent anterad, carinate, slightly shorter than eye length; in lateral view (Fig. 2) convex and declivous anterad. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum (
Fig. 1
) as long as pronotum; surface with transverse striae; scutellum flat.
